introduce of akatski node 
Akatsuki is a web app that lets users create and manage their tasks.

Installation
To install Akatsuki, you need to have Node.js and MongoDB installed on your system. You can download Node.js from https://nodejs.org/en/download/ and MongoDB from https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community.

To run Akatsuki, simply clone this repository and execute the following commands:

npm install
npm start
Copy
Usage
Akatsuki allows users to add, edit, delete, and mark tasks as done. Users can also filter tasks by status or search for tasks by keywords.

